description:
&lt;p&gt;A fixed term Band 6 Occupational Therapist vacancy has arisen in our Trauma and Orthopaedic team to provide maternity cover.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will primarily be to support the rehabilitation and discharge of patients following trauma, but will also have responsibility for providing therapy for paediatric patients on our children’s ward, and the clinical support of Band 4 therapy assistants on Orthopaedic Elective Surgery ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have significant post-graduate, orthopaedics experience, and experience of managing patients with complex needs, and patients receiving end of life care would be beneficial. You will need to accommodate a busy schedule, in conjunction with a strong, well-established multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will demonstrate sound clinical knowledge, creative and innovative treatment planning and an understanding of the demands on the acute setting. You will have advanced organisational and time management skills, experience of staff supervision, management of a small team, and a commitment and passion for supporting patients through their acute care and rehabilitation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is part of an integrated seven day working service therefore a willingness to work in this way is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Megan Harper - Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:megan.harper1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:01384 456111 Ext 4580&lt;/p&gt;
